’Ł@7d57778223e351209bcb497d3071d7deedc7a92c8518be8cfed822a4303268d3ŚeTitle: title: decode base64
Path: Examples
Content:
Decode a Base64 string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "U29tZSBEYXRh" | decode base64 | decode


```
Decode arbitrary data
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "/w==" | decode base64
Length: 1 (0x1) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   ff                                                   Ć—


```
Decode a URL-safe Base64 string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "_w==" | decode base64 --url
Length: 1 (0x1) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   ff                                                   Ć—


```
’Ł@631b961c843063197c18060192081689e0e10a2757c4fdb5a0a3eb85890ef262ŁøTitle: title: decode base64
Path: Notes
Content:
The default alphabet is taken from RFC 4648, section 4.  A URL-safe version is available.
Note this command will collect stream input.
